</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The SCP Wiki Needs Your Help to #StandWithSCPRU! The wiki is, essentially, under attack - Andrey Duskin, who you may remember from some months ago for trying to copyright the SCP logo, is back. This time, he's trying to extort SCP-RU into making him an admin and turning the wiki into a glorified advertisement. With your help, we've raised over $50,000 for legal funds, which you can still contribute to here: <a href="http://scp.bz/fundraiser">http://scp.bz/fundraiser</a> While the fight isn't over yet, everyone's support has been amazing. For more information, go here: <a href="http://scp.bz/standwithru">http://scp.bz/standwithru</a></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>We here in the Site News hope you've had an awesome Halloween season here on this most spooky of websites!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Check the <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-10752847/seminars-and-workshops#post-4193637">Seminars and Workshops</a></strong> post for schedule of upcoming events.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3636">SCP-3636</a> - (&quot;World's Greatest Jukebox&quot;) - <em>The jukebox was found undamaged with the screen showing a video of the fire from the bar's exterior while playing the song &quot;We Didn't Start the Fire&quot; by Billy Joel.</em> Written by GerrymanderBassist</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/letters-to-my-future-self">letters to my future self</a> - <em>&quot;On 2014/04/30, a series of notes written on paper scraps were recovered from PoI-████'s temporary holding cell.&quot;</em> Written by AthosNetwork.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/spc-2922">SPC-2922</a> - <em>TEETH-FILLED VOID is a desert within Corbenic that is perpetually night.</em> Written by Stormbreath.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4436">SCP-4436</a> - (&quot;Jesus Saves&quot;) - <em>SCP-4436 is an large active distributed database, presently stored in an array of supercomputers located at Site-48.</em> Written by spikebrennan, selected by <em>MacWarren.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4389-j">SCP-4389-J</a> - (&quot;Can the Foundation do THIS?&quot;) - <em>The anomalous effect of SCP-4389-J varies in potency depending on how long a member of personnel has been employed at the Foundation.</em> Written by gee0765, selected by <em>gee0765.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
